other_tests.findings: The appendix is dilated measuring up to 10 mm, fluid-filled and with a hyperemic wall, progressed since the study from yesterday. There is no abscess formation and no appendicolith. The remainder of the partially visualized large bowel is normal. The urinary bladder and uterus are normal. Very trace pelvic free fluid is noted. No drainable fluid collection or extraluminal gas seen. The ovaries appear normal. No suspicious lytic or sclerotic bony lesions.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The findings of the appendix being dilated and hyperemic progressed since the study from yesterday.
